<a name="1071"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">World's Largest Consumer Technology Tradeshow, Again!</div>
<br />
<IMG height=116 hspace=8 src="/print/images/content/Veris_logo.gif" width=82 align=right>An independent audit, performedby VERIS Consulting LLC, verified all attendance numbers and confirmed the International CES as the world's largest consumer technology tradeshow and America's largest annual tradeshow of any kind. Three thousand exhibitors showcased their latest products on more than 1.8 million net square feet of exhibit space, with a total of 141,150 in attendance. CES also grew its international attendance of industry professionals to a new high of 28,000, a nearly four percent increase over last year, during the industry tradeshow's four-day run.<BR><BR></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: ">CES attracts the "who's who" of the technology and related industries, including C-level executives from the entertainment, wireless and consumer electronics industries. The attendees at the 2008 show make up 95 percent ($153 billion) of the U.S. industry's buying power. <BR><BR>Keep an eye out for your copy of the 2008&nbsp; Audit Summary Results!<BR><BR><STRONG>2008 International CES Attendees</STRONG> 
<UL>
<LI>Exhibits Only Attendees: 75,491 </LI>
<LI>Exhibitors: 49,572 </LI>
<LI>Conference Attendees: 8,817 </LI>
<LI>Press: 4,630 </LI>
<LI>Financial and Market Analysts: 1,974 </LI>
<LI>Speakers: 380 </LI>
<LI><STRONG>Total: 141,150</STRONG></LI></UL></SPAN>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
