<a name="1070"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Meet Your Exhibitor Advisory Board</div>
<br />
<IMG height=150 hspace=8 src="/print/images/content/EAB_Logo.gif" width=150 align=right>The <A href="/print/exhibitors/resources/advisoryBoard.asp">CES Exhibitor Advisory Board (EAB)</A> is your gateway to show management. As CES exhibitors, they continue to serve on the behalf of all exhibiting companies, working collectively with the CES organization on everything from housing to transportation and labor to policy changes. Having the EAB provide feedback and suggestions to the CES team optimizes the experience for all. The EAB is available to talk with any exhibitor regarding the successes or issues you face in your exhibit experience. <BR><BR><A href="/print/exhibitors/resources/advisoryBoard.asp">We encourage you to get in touch with the board</A> at any time of the year (on-site at CES or via e-mail, phone, etc.) to not only keep them informed as your representatives, but also to learn more about the CES Exhibitor Advisory Board and how to get involved.

